initial statement:
 1036
Your Honor,

I stand before you today, pleading guilty to the charge of careless driving. I am deeply remorseful for my actions and understand the gravity of the situation.

On the day in question, I was on my way to the airport to pick up my family members. Due to the urgency of the situation, I made the ill-advised decision to drive aggressively and at a speed higher than what was permitted. Additionally, I must acknowledge that I made the irresponsible choice of answering a text message while driving. As a result, I collided with a guardrail. Thankfully, no one else was injured.

In reflecting upon this incident, I now fully comprehend the danger I put myself and others in. I acknowledge that my actions were inexcusable and could have resulted in serious harm or even worse consequences. I take full responsibility for my behavior and express my sincerest apologies for any distress or inconvenience I may have caused.

I would like to bring to the court's attention that I am 37 years old and have maintained an otherwise clean record prior to this incident. I have never been involved in any criminal activities and have strived to live a responsible and law-abiding life. Furthermore, I want to emphasize that I am an active supporter of the British Heart Foundation, regularly making contributions to help those in need.

As I move forward, I understand the importance of learning from my mistakes. I am committed to taking the necessary steps to prevent such negligence from happening again. I recognize the need to improve my driving habits, exercise more caution on the road, and refrain from any distractions.

In conclusion, I humbly request the court's leniency and understanding in considering my plea in mitigation. I am fully aware of the consequences of my actions and will diligently make amends to ensure that such negligence is never repeated. Thank you for your time and consideration.

Sincerely,

Charlotte Porter
