I respectfully come before you today to accept full accountability for my actions and enter a plea of guilty to the charge of careless driving. I deeply regret the events that unfolded on the day in question and acknowledge the potential harm that could have resulted from my imprudent behavior.

On the day of the incident, I was rushing to the airport to pick up my family members. Fueled by the urgency to reach my destination, I regrettably drove aggressively and surpassed the speed limit. Furthermore, I made a grave error in judgment by responding to a text message from my cousin while behind the wheel. Tragically, these actions led to a collision with a guardrail. Thankfully, no other individuals were harmed as a consequence of the accident.

By pleading guilty, I humbly demonstrate my understanding of the serious nature of my actions and my commitment to accepting the penalties. My aim is to spare the court unnecessary time and resources that would be expended during a trial.

Upon reflecting on this unfortunate incident, I now fully grasp the gravity of my behavior and the potential danger it posed not only to myself but also to fellow road users. I extend my sincerest apologies for any inconvenience or distress caused due to my reckless actions on that fateful day.

In conclusion, I kindly request your understanding and leniency, taking into consideration my previously unblemished record. I assure you that I will make road safety paramount in my life going forward.

Thank you for your consideration.

Yours faithfully,
Charlotte Porter
